01/07/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The government on Monday (30 June) endorsed the text of the bilateral agreement with the United States that would bar extradition of nationals from both countries to the International Criminal Court (ICC).
Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva and US Ambassador to Macedonia Lawrence Butler will likely sign the document Tuesday.
A total of 43 countries worldwide have sealed the accord, including Romania, Albania and Bosnia and Herzegovina.
In other news, Skopje is hosting a three-day meeting organised by the International Red Cross, aimed at enhancing army efforts to protect civilians during war.
Delegations from 16 Balkan and Baltic countries are attending.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 01/07/03;
MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 30/06/03)
